This paper is primarily focused on the performance of stochastic gradient descent (SGD) on optimization problems, which is a topic within the machine learning community. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.LG (Machine Learning). The paper also involves analyzing the expected optimization error, which is a topic within information theory (cs.IT) and numerical analysis (cs.NA). Additionally, the paper involves analyzing the performance of different heuristics, which is a topic within data structures (cs.DS) and control systems (cs.SY).
